When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
Thought:I would like to use remote repository when am sure it is correct and has no bugs and ready to allow others view.
Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
Thought:Manual pulling gives you more control and helps you organise your work better while automatic pulling gives less control.
Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?
Thought:-Fork is a command used to copy a reopsitory from another person's account to yours on github.I would use it  when I want 			to copy a repository and keep it online without having to download it in my computer.
		-Clone is a command used to copy a repository from Github to your computer.
		-Branch is a commend used to create a different part to store commits in my repository.
What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote stored locally?
Thought:In order to be able to fix conflicts when trying to merge.
How would you collaborate without using Git or GitHub? What would be easier, and what would be harder?
Thought:The only way collaborate without those is using social media. I would be harder because it would be difficult to locate the 		changes made to code and request changes.
When would you want to make changes in a separate branch rather than directly in master? What benefits does each approach have?
Thought:I would to make changes in a separate branch when I don't want the main branch to be affected by my change incase any 				problem arises.